Rating: 3
This soup is wonderful. I subbed half the water for apple cider and added a bit of cardamom & nutmeg. The bacon added a great contrast to the sweetness.

Rating: 4
Everyone loved this soup! I used vegetable oil instead of bacon, and didn't add any garnishes. The 1/2 tsp pepper gave it a good kick - I would use less next time, and will use either white pepper or cayenne to avoid black specks. It took about 40 minutes to cook everything down before it was pureed.

Rating: 4
Great recipe! I increase the apple flavor by deglazing with some apple cider. Don't forget - you can use an immersion blender instead of a regular blender. I think they are easier to clean (dishwasher safe!).